This paper proposes a method for optimizing convolution neural network models for image classification tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves using a tree classifier, which is a machine learning technique that falls under the category of supervised learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a multi-kernel SVM plus classifier, which is a type of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural network (cs.NE) technique. Finally, the paper discusses the speedup ratio achieved by the proposed method, which is a performance metric that is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
